[{"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Bavarian State Ministry of Finance38 - S-1300 - 109/65 - 61275bek"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "OFD N\u00fcrnberg S-1300 - 124 / St 21 vom 16/12 / 94S-1300S-1300 - 5 - St 112S-1300 -EStK Annex DBA advance card for card 11 Bibliography of the corresponding administrative instructions: BrandenburgOFD Cottbus S-1300 - 5 - St 112 dated 25/01 / 95OECD-MA: 15 Taxation of foreign income for natural persons with unlimited tax liability (Guide - Version: November 1994) 1 General information 11 Important provisions of the tax code 12 Unlimited tax liability 13 Calculation of foreign income 14 Determination and proof of foreign income and foreign taxes 15 Conversion of foreign income and taxes2 Avoidance of double taxation (basic rules) 21 Credit method22 Exemption method3 Foreign income from a country with which a double taxation agreement exists31 General information on the double taxation agreements311 Existing double taxation agreements312 Structure of the double taxation agreements313 Taxation rules of the double taxation agreements32 Residence33 Crediting of foreign taxes (crediting method) 331 General332 Implementation of the crediting333 Additional information on individual types of income34 Exemption from foreign income (exemption method) 341 General342 Reservation of progression343 Additional information on individual types of income4 Foreign income from a country with which there is no double taxation agreement41 Determination of income42 Offsetting of foreign taxes43 Flat rate waiver5 Negative foreign income51 Limitation of loss compensation and deduction in accordance with Section 2a 1 and 2 EStG52 Deduction of losses according to \u00a7 2a Abs 3 and 4 EStG (until 1990: \u00a7 2 AIG) 6 Taxation abroad contrary to the agreement7 Evaluation of the notification according to \u00a7 18 AStG8 Special procedural features in the separate and uniform determination of foreign income81 General82 Deduction of foreign