ion of the remaining losses18 Constitutionality2 Loss deduction according to \u00a7 2a Paragraphs 3 and 422 Income deduction according to \u00a7 2a Paragraph 3 and 422 Income from the state24 Application25 Separate determination26 Progression reservation27 Subsequent taxation28 Monitoring3 Universal successionAnnex 2: Overview of withholding tax ratesAbbreviations IG = Foreign Investment ActAStG = Foreign Tax ActDBA = Double Taxation AgreementEStH = Income Tax Manual 1993OECD MA = OECD Model Agreement 1992 to avoid double taxation of income and tax liability in the area of \u200b\u200btaxation (RI) / AWD = law of the international economy (formerly foreign trade ftsdienst des Betriebsberater) BB = Betriebsberater) Table of contents 1 General information 11 Important provisions of the tax code In the case of matters affecting foreign countries, the provisions of the AO must be observed, including the following special provisions: Section 2 AO on the priority of international agreements (DTA and other international agreements), Section 90 (2) AO on the increased obligation to cooperate on the part of those involved, Section 93 AO on the obligation to provide information on the parties involved and other persons, Section 117 AO on intergovernmental legal and administrative assistance in tax matters, Section 138 (2) AO on the obligation to notify the establishment and acquisition of foreign companies and permanent establishments as well as the Acquisition of foreign participations (corresponding declaration obligation within the framework of the form annex AUS 1993 and 1994 ESt 1 B 1993 and 1994), \u00a7 160 AO on the naming of creditors and payees, \u00a7 162 Abs 2 AO on the estimation of tax bases in the event of a breach of the duty to cooperate \u00a7 9 0 Paragraph 2 AO, Section 165 Paragraph 1 Sentence 2 No. 1 AO on the possibility of provisional tax assessment in the event of uncertainty about the entry into force of DTAs, Section 175a AO on the implementation of a mutual agreement or an arbitration award, Section 180 Paragraph 5 AO on the separate determination of foreign Income that is exempt from taxation according to a double taxation agreement, but is important for the tax assessment (no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "8), \u00a7 354 Paragraph 1 a AO on the waiver of legal remedies regarding"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the tax bases, which can be of importance for a mutual agreement or an arbitration procedure, \u00a7 362 Abs 1 a AO on the withdrawal of a legal remedy with regard to the tax bases, which can be of importance for a mutual agreement or an arbitration procedure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "12 Unrestricted tax liability Natural persons who have a domicile or habitual abode in Germany are subject to unlimited income tax liability on all domestic and foreign income (world income principle, H 1 EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Regarding the terms \"domicile\" and \"habitual residence\" - the AO application decree for \u00a7\u00a7 8 9 AO (AO card index)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The scope of taxation can in particular be restricted by a DTA"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "13 Approach of foreign income The foreign income must be income that is subject to income tax according to \u00a7 2 Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 7 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A DTA cannot justify a domestic tax liability, but only leave a tax claim of the Federal Republic of Germany based on domestic tax law or withdraw it in whole or in part"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "14 Determination and proof of foreign income and foreign taxes The type and amount of foreign income must always be determined in accordance with German law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Operating expenses and advertising expenses (also possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Lump sums) are to be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "References to foreign income can also be found in documents in the files, in particular from control material and confirmations of domicile in Germany (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Certificates of residence) that have been submitted in connection with applications for exemption or reimbursement of foreign withholding taxes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer must provide evidence of the amount of foreign income and the determination and payment of foreign taxes by means of appropriate documents (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Tax assessment, payment receipt), if necessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "in German translation (\u00a7 68b EStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the tax is only registered abroad by an employer or entrepreneur, a certificate from the registering party about the amount of the tax paid is sufficient as evidence (H 212a (assessment of foreign taxes) EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "15 Conversion of foreign income and taxes In the case of excess income (Section 2 Paragraph 1 No. 4 to 7 EStG), income and income-related expenses in foreign currency must be regularly converted at the rate at the time of inflow or outflow"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a purchase transaction in a foreign currency (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "House purchase) the exchange rate at the time of purchase is decisive for the calculation of the purchase costs (R 32a Paragraph 2 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A foreign tax must be converted using the rate applicable on the day of payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The official exchange rate in the Federal Gazette is decisive (R 212a Paragraph 1 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplicity, conversion at the sales tax conversion rates that are published monthly in the Federal Tax Gazette Part I is permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "2 Avoidance of double taxation (basic rules) Foreign income is usually also subject to taxation abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "To compensate, they are not taxed or only taxed at a reduced rate in the Federal Republic of Germany (avoidance of double taxation)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The following methods are particularly suitable: offsetting the foreign tax against the German tax that is attributable to the foreign income; (Section 34c (1) EStG) Credit method -; the exemption, d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the removal of foreign income from the German tax base using the progression proviso (Section 32b (1) No. 2 EStG) exemption method -"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "An overview of the tax exemptions and tax reductions for foreign income is contained in Appendix 121 Credit method The credit method is to be used if a DBA is not available (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "42) exists, for the income for which the DBA provides for crediting (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "With the credit method, the foreign income is included in the assessment basis for the German income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This applies to both positive and negative income, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the latter are to be allowed to compensate for other income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The restrictions of Section 2a (1) and (2) EStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "51) must be observed, however"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The tax levied in the foreign country can either be offset or deducted upon request when determining the income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If no double taxation agreement is applicable, this follows for all foreign income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 34d EStG from \u00a7 34c Paragraph 1 and 2 EStG, otherwise from the relevant regulations of the respective DBA in conjunction with \u00a7 34c Paragraph 6 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A deduction is also permitted when determining the income in accordance with Section 34c (2) EStG if the DBA expressly only mentions crediting (R 212d EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "22 Exemption method The exemption method is only to be used if this is provided for in a double tax agreement (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "341)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A crediting of foreign taxes or a deduction when determining income is not possible in this case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "With the exemption method, the foreign income is treated as tax-free, but when calculating the tax rate within the scope of the progression proviso in accordance with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 32b (1) no.2 EStG is taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "According to this, both the positive and the negative progression proviso is possible, the latter to the effect that losses may increase the tax rate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "decrease to 0"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The restrictions of Section 2a (1) and (2) EStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "51) must be observed, however"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3 Foreign income from a country with which a DTA exists31 General information on the DTA311 Existing DTA3111 Status of the DTA An overview of the current status of the DTA and DTA negotiations is published in BStBl Part I at the beginning of each year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "As of 1 1 1994 Annex 10 EStH 1993 According to the BMF letter of 3 1 1994 (BStBl 1994 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "7) the following rules also apply in addition: 3112 Validity of the double taxation agreements in the new federal states The agreements concluded by the Federal Republic of Germany also apply from 1 January 1991 to the five new federal states incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Berlin"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The double taxation agreements of the former GDR that existed on October 2, 1990 (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of the multilateral agreements with the Comecon countries) are only applied until 31 December 1990"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3113 DTA with the former Soviet Union The German-Soviet DTA from 1981 applies until further notice for the Russian Federation, Ukraine, the Republic of Belarus, the Republic of Armenia, the Republic of Azerbaijan, the Republic of Kazakhstan, Turkmenistan, the Republic of Uzbekistan, the Republic of Moldova, the Republic of Kyrgyzstan, the Republic of Tajikistan and the Republic of Georgia"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In relation to the Baltic states (the republics of Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania) the German-Soviet DTA does not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Until the conclusion of new agreements - planned with these states - there is currently no agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3114 DTA with Yugoslavia The German-Yugoslav DTA from 1987 continues to apply until further notice in relation to Croatia, Slovenia, Bosnia-Herzegovina, Macedonia and the former Yugoslavia"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3115 DTA with the former Czechoslovakia The German-Czechoslovak DTA from 1980 continues to apply to the Czech Republic and the Slovak Republic"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Most of the DTAs are structured as follows: The introductory provisions delimit the scope of the agreement and contain the definitions that are important for its application (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Residence, permanent establishment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The following articles set the framework within which the source state may tax income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Another article determines how the state of residence avoids double taxation on income, which the source state may also tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The final articles regulate the protection against tax discrimination, the implementation of mutual agreement procedures, the exchange of information between the contracting states as well as the entry into force and expiry of the agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It should be noted that individual DBA provisions in additional agreements (final protocol, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": ") can be modified or explained"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "313 Taxation rules of the DBA The rules on taxation in the source country generally do not allow any conclusions to be drawn about taxation in the country of residence or the avoidance of double taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This can be found regularly in the article on avoiding double taxation in the country of residence (also No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as \"can\" and / or \"may\" are mentioned in the regulation of taxation law in a DTA, the respective regulation only refers to the specifically addressed contracting state"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the latter does not make use of the permit, i.e. does not exercise his right to tax, the other contracting state generally has no right to tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The other contracting state is therefore also limited in this case to the right to tax that the DTA expressly leaves it (prohibition of virtual double taxation)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "32 Residency Unlimited Stpfl are also i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of the respective double taxation agreement resident in the Federal Republic of Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Does the here unrestricted Stpfl also have a domicile or habitual abode in the foreign country (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Dual residence), it should be noted that the DTA determines one of the two states, which is i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of the agreement applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, this is the state with which the Stpfl has closer personal and economic relationships (center of life interests)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the Federal Republic of Germany is not the country of residence in the case of dual residence, there is usually no right to tax the foreign income in Germany (also from third countries)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "These are also not subject to the progression proviso"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The personal unrestricted tax liability in Germany remains unaffected, as far as Germany the income z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "may tax based on the location"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Residency abroad is only assumed for the application of the double taxation agreement (AO application decree on \u00a7 8 No. 2 1 sentence, AO card index)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Special feature: American citizens who are resident in Germany are subject to unlimited tax liability both in Germany and - due to their nationality - in the USA (Protocol Section 1 to Art"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "1 and Art"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "23 para 3 DBA USA 1989)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the Federal Republic of Germany is the state of residence or if it is considered as such in the case of dual residence, it must first be determined in accordance with the articles on taxation in the source state whether the foreign state has a right to tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the foreign state has no right to tax, the income must be recorded in the Federal Republic of Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It must be ensured that the foreign income is also included in the respective annexes to the income tax return and in the designated Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "be transmitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "13 must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Crediting or deduction of foreign taxes is ruled out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If, according to the articles on withholding taxation, the foreign state may also tax this income, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "No statement has yet been made on how double taxation will be avoided in the Federal Republic of Germany (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "313)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The avoidance of double taxation in the country of residence is regulated in a separate article of the agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The DTAs use two methods: the credit method and the exemption method (no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "21 and 22)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "33 Crediting of foreign taxes (crediting method) 331 General The crediting method (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "21) applies according to the DBA i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of income from dividends, interest and license fees (if there is a right to withholding tax), from work as an artist or professional athlete, from work as a member of the supervisory and administrative board of a foreign company from immovable property in exceptional cases (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Switzerland, Spain)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Income is included in Germany when determining the total amount of income; Section 2a (1) and (2) EStG must be observed (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "21 51)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "332 Implementation of the crediting Only the fixed, paid foreign tax that is no longer subject to a reduction claim in accordance with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 34c Paragraph 6 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "V can be credited with Paragraph 1 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The proportionate German income tax attributable to the foreign income is to be determined for the total of the income originating from one country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The income and the resulting foreign taxes are listed separately in Annex AUS 1993 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2910 -11 to -24 -25"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "From 1994, for the first time, a distinction is made in Annex AUS 1994 for taxable foreign income between income from capital assets and other types of income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For foreign income from capital assets - Appendix 1 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "14 The income from other types of income and the foreign taxes to be offset are listed in Annex AUS 1994 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2910 -11 to -26 -27"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The calculation of the maximum amount in accordance with Section 34c (1) EStG is based on the foreign income that is taken into account when determining the taxable income, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "after application of \u00a7 2a Abs 1 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The foreign taxes to be offset are also to be included in the foreign taxes that have been paid on income within the meaning of Section 2a (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "As a result, in cases in which, on the basis of Section 2a (1) EStG, total income from a state is not to be taken into account when determining the total amount of income (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Losses from silent participation), which may be applied to foreign income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "foreign taxes levied within the framework of the maximum amount according to \u00a7 34c paragraph 1 EStG or deducted at the request of the taxpayer according to \u00a7 34c paragraph 2 EStG when determining the income (R 212a paragraph 2 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The deduction under Section 34c (2) EStG increases the negative foreign income that cannot be compensated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The right to choose must be exercised uniformly for all income from a foreign country and for all taxes that can be offset under the respective double taxation agreement (R 212c EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The application of Section 34c (3) EStG is out of the question here"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a deduction in accordance with Section 34c (2) EStG, the AUS 1993 annex at Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2984 enter the number of the country for which the foreign tax was deducted when determining the income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "333 Additional information on individual types of income Details on foreign income from dividends and interest are shown in Appendix 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For foreign income from private property, if the credit method is used as an exception (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Switzerland, Spain), see Appendix 234 Exemption from foreign income (exemption method) 341 General The exemption method (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "22) applies according to the DBA i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of income from commercial operations (corporate profits from permanent establishments), employment (unless the so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "183-day rule applies), self-employed work within the framework of a permanent establishment, immovable property (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Agriculture and Forestry)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The income is treated as tax-free, but when calculating the tax rate within the framework of the progression proviso in accordance with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 32b (1) no.2 EStG is taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Individual agreements grant tax exemption for permanent establishment profits only if the income of the permanent establishment comes from certain active activities (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Activity clause)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "342 Progression reservation The type and amount of foreign income must also be determined for the purpose of the progression reservation under German tax law (H 185 (Foreign Income) EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Operating expenses and advertising expenses (also possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Lump sums) must therefore be deducted when calculating the income to be taken into account in the progression proviso (tax rate income)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "These operating expenses or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Business expenses may not reduce domestic income (Section 3c EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "To determine the tax rate income, the income tax assessment must always be carried out in 2 stages: Stage: Determination of the taxable income Stage: Calculation of the special tax rate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The following special features should be noted: The tax bases that depend on the amount of income, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Age relief (Section 24a EStG) and the tax exemption for farmers and foresters (Section 13 (3) EStG) must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The prohibition of deduction according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 10 (2) No. 1 EStG 1990 does not apply (BFH judgment of April 29, 1992 BStBl 1993 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "149)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a negative total amount of income and at the same time a positive progression reservation, the BFH judgment of 13 11 1991 BStBl 1992 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "345 to apply (H 185 (foreign losses) example 1 EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "On the basis of assessment in the case of a loss carried back or carried forward analogous to \u00a7 10d EStG - BFH judgment of 11 October 1989 (BStBl 1990 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "157)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Does the tax-free foreign income contain extraordinary income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7\u00a7 34 34b EStG, this income is excluded from the application of the progression proviso, but it is not included in the determination of a possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "reduced tax rate according to \u00a7\u00a7 34 Abs 2 34b and 34c Abs 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In addition to capital gains in accordance with Section 34 (2) of the Income Tax Act (EStG), extraordinary income also includes remuneration for several years of work abroad in the sense of"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 34 Abs 3 EStG (BFH judgment of 9 6 1993 BStBl 1993 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "790)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The extraordinary income is to be found in Annex AUS 1993 and 1994 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2967 to be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the cases of Section 2a (1) EStG (in detail no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "51 and Appendix 4 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "26) the negative progression reservation is excluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The income subject to the progression proviso is to be found in Annex AUS 1993 and 1994 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2960 to -64 to be entered separately according to state, source of income and type of income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "However, as far as wages are available, the income in Appendix N 1993 and 1994 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "47/4839 and the advertising expenses at Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "87/8857 to be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "(According to the DBA Italy of 18 January 1989, which must be applied from 1 November 1993, the progression proviso now also applies in relation to Italy"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": ") 343 Supplementary information on individual types of income Details on foreign income from private property are given in Appendix 2 and on foreign income from employment in Appendix 3"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "4 Foreign income from a country with which there is no double taxation agreement41 Determination of income When determining the sum of domestic income, all foreign positive and negative income is recorded (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "World income principle), exception: Appendix 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3 \u00a7 2a Abs 1 and 2 EStG must be observed (in detail no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "51 and Appendix 4)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "42 Crediting of foreign taxes The fixed, paid foreign tax that is no longer subject to a reduction claim is credited in accordance with Section 34c (1) EStG, if foreign income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "34d EStG are present, the source country is also the taxation country and the foreign tax corresponds to the German income tax (Annex 8 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The remarks on No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "332 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The maximum amount limit according to \u00a7 34c Paragraph 1 Sentences 1 and 2 EStG (maximum crediting up to the amount of the proportionate German income tax applicable to the income from a foreign country) makes it necessary to calculate the maximum amounts separately for each country (\u00a7 68a Sentence 2 EStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "When determining the maximum amount, flat-rate foreign income (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "43) and the flat rate tax out of consideration (R 212b EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the application according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 34c (2) EStG, instead of deducting the foreign tax when calculating the income, this application can only be made uniformly for all income from a specific country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "(In this case, the number of the state to which the application relates is in Annex AUS 1993, at Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2984 to be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": ") Regarding the processing instructions, no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "332 Are the o"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Requirements for crediting or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "a deduction according to \u00a7 34c Abs 1 or 2 EStG is not available, the foreign tax is acc"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 34c (3) EStG must always be deducted as business expenses or business expenses when determining the income of the respective type of income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It is important to ensure that the taxable income from the AUS 1993 and 1994 appendix is \u200b\u200balso included in the corresponding GSE, KSO, L, N and / or V appendices"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "43 Flat rate waiver on the so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Flat-rate decree and the special regulations contained therein for foreign income from commercial operations and self-employed work are pointed out (Appendix 20 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "According to this, under certain conditions, the foreign income is only reduced to 25% upon request"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "taxed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The FA is responsible for the flat rate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The lump-sum income is to be found in Annex AUS 1993 and 1994 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2938 to be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "5 Negative foreign income Section 2a EStG regulates two different facts: While Section 2a Paragraphs 1 and 2 EStG restricts loss compensation and deduction for certain negative foreign income, Section 2a Section 3 EStG allows loss compensation and deduction for negative foreign permanent establishment income under certain conditions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "51 Restriction of loss compensation and deduction according to \u00a7 2a Paragraph 1 and 2 EStG \u00a7 2a Paragraph 1 EStG restricts certain negative income from foreign sources (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "11 in Appendix 4) the loss compensation and the loss deduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply to negative income from an active commercial establishment abroad as well as certain negative income / profit reductions from shares in an active commercial foreign corporation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant for what reasons the losses occurred abroad (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Storms, force majeure)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of losses that are not expressly mentioned in Section 2a (1) EStG, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "from self-employment, loss compensation is possible with all domestic income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The limited loss compensation means that negative income can only be offset against positive income of the same type from the same country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "They may not be deducted according to Section 10d EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If a loss compensation is not possible, the losses reduce the positive foreign income of the same type that the Stpfl receives in the following assessment periods from the same country (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "limited loss carryforward)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For negative income from assessment periods before 1992, the ability to carry forward losses is limited to seven years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If other provisions of the Income Tax Act already restrict loss compensation (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "in the case of losses from commercial animal husbandry in accordance with Section 15 (4) EStG or in the event of losses from participation in a foreign partnership with limited liability in accordance with Section 15a EStG, R 138d (4) EStR 1993), the provision with the further restriction applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The regulations in Section 2a (1) and (2) EStG have the following effect: a) Directly on the tax base (limited loss compensation prohibition) if the negative income comes from countries with which there is no double taxation agreement or a double taxation agreement exists if the income is not based on the credit method are exempt from domestic taxation, b) within the scope of the progression proviso on the tax rate, if in the DBA case the income remains tax-free in accordance with the exemption method in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This means that with negative income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Abs 1 EStG the negative progression reservation is excluded (H 185 (foreign losses) EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Supplementary information in Appendix 4 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "11 to 19 and no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3 and Annexes 3 and 452 Loss deduction according to \u00a7 2a Abs 3 and 4 EStG (until 1990: \u00a7 2 AIG) According to the DBA, commercial permanent establishment income in Germany i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "optional"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The consequence of this is that losses only have an effect in the event of a negative progression reservation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 2a (3) EStG enables, on application - instead of the negative progression proviso - loss compensation and loss deduction for losses from commercial establishments in a foreign country with which a double taxation agreement exists, if the income is tax-exempt under the double taxation agreement in Germany and the activity requirements of \u00a7 2a Paragraph 2 of the Income Tax Act are fulfilled"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If a loss is not offset in the same assessment period, Section 10d EStG shall apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "So that the regulation does not lead to a tax break compared to a situation without an agreement, subsequent taxation is to be carried out - for an unlimited period - if, in a later assessment period, overall positive commercial income is generated from this state (therefore i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "only forbearance)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In accordance with Section 2a (4) EStG, subsequent taxation can also be considered when converting the foreign permanent establishment into a corporation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, there is no subsequent taxation if the taxpayer proves that it is generally not possible to carry forward or carry back losses in a foreign country (Section 2a (3) sentence 4 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Supplementary information in Appendix 4 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "21 to 28 and no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3 and Appendices 3 to 56 Taxation abroad contrary to the treaty Taxation in the source country that contradicts the provisions of a DTA cannot normally be taken into account for domestic taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The crediting of wrongly levied taxes cannot be claimed according to Section 34c (6) sentence 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It is the sole responsibility of the Stpfl to assert claims for reimbursement and reduction against the foreign tax authorities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the event of taxation contrary to the treaty, the taxpayer generally has the option of filing legal remedies abroad or of requesting the initiation of a mutual agreement procedure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The application to initiate a mutual agreement procedure can be submitted to the tax office responsible for taxation or to the Federal Ministry of Finance as the competent authority"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Reference is made to the BMF's leaflet on the international mutual agreement procedure dated 1 4 1993 (BStBl 1993 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "332, 1994 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "136)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The Federal Office of Finance, Friedhofstrasse 1 53225 Bonn, or the account-keeping institute has applications ready for reimbursement of foreign withholding tax on dividends and interest that has been levied too much (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "13 Appendix 1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Please note that the so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Certificate of residence (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "14) is to be issued"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "7 Evaluation of the notification according to \u00a7 18 AStG The tax bases for \u00a7\u00a7 7 - 14 AStG are separately and if necessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "uniformly determined by the responsible tax office (OFD Munich: by the FA Munich for corporations and the FA Augsburg-Stadt)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The additional amount is to be applied to income from capital assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the shares in the foreign company belong to business assets, the additional amount increases the profit (Section 10 (2) AStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Further details, esp"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "on tax reimbursement in accordance with Section 11 (2) and (3) AStG can be found in the application letter for the AStG, which will soon be published in BStBl Part I."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "8 Special features of procedural law in the separate and uniform determination of foreign income81 General"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "to be determined separately and uniformly (Section 180 there also Paragraph 5 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "That applies u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "if a domestic partnership generates such income or if several tax residents are involved in foreign partnerships"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the latter case, the participation must be reported to the Federal Office of Finance using form BfF 2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the local jurisdiction for the separate and uniform determination of the profits of foreign partnerships in which domestic shareholders are involved - BMF letter dated 11 12 1989 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "470 (AO index \u00a7 25)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The amount of foreign taxes to be offset must also be determined separately and uniformly (BFH judgment of 18 7 1990 BStBl 1990 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "951)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Due to the regulations of \u00a7 34c EStG on the offsetting of foreign taxes against the ESt, it is necessary to determine the foreign income and the foreign taxes due on it separately for each country (column 12 of the annex ESt 1 2 3 B 1993 and 1994 communication ESt 4 B 1993 and 1994)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The state from which the income originates and from which the foreign taxes were set must be specified"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as notifications are received by the tax offices of the domicile about the results of a determination that do not meet the requirements set out above, the respective tax office must be asked to provide additional determinations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "82 Deduction of foreign taxes in accordance with Section 34c (2) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) In cases of separate and uniform assessment, each party involved can submit an application for the deduction of foreign taxes in accordance with Section 34c (2) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The Stpfl must exercise his right to apply for all income and taxes from the same state in a uniform manner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the income is determined separately, the tax deduction must be decided in the determination procedure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The application must be made in the declaration of assessment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In cases of uniform and separate determination, each party can submit an application"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If, in addition to the income to be determined, a taxpayer has received other foreign income from the same country as an individual and / or as a participant in an assessment period, the exercise or non-exercise of the right of application in the assessment or tax return first received by the responsible tax office is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Until the decision issued in this procedure cannot be contested, the application can be made up or withdrawn (R 212c EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "83 Special features of Section 2a EStG If foreign income is to be determined separately and uniformly, it must be decided in the assessment procedure whether this income is within the meaning of Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 7 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Since legal consequences from \u00a7 2a EStG arise exclusively in the case of the income tax assessment of the parties involved in the determination, in addition to the amount of the income, it must also be determined which type of income is to be allocated within the meaning of \u00a7 2a Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 7 EStG and from which country this income is allocated originate (Column 10 and 11 of Annex ESt 1 2 3 B 1993 and 1994 Communication ESt 4 B 1993 and 1994)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "From this it becomes clear that the determination of negative income within the meaning of Section 2a Paragraph 1 EStG cannot be dispensed with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the income to be exempted is not from commercial establishments, a distinction must only be made between current and extraordinary income (column 7 of Annex ESt 1 2 3 B 1993 and 1994 communication ESt 4 B 1993 and 1994); Furthermore, the regulations of Section 2a Paragraphs 1 and 2 EStG must be observed (column 11 of Annex 1 2 3 B 1993 and 1994, ESt 4 B 1993 and 1994 communication)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the determination procedure it is only necessary to decide whether and to what extent the permanent establishment income meets the requirements of Section 2a Paragraph 3 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "V with paragraph 1 u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "2 EStG and from which country this income comes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A summary of the permanent establishment income from several countries is therefore not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For these reasons, the taxation criteria for the case of the loss deduction according to \u00a7 2a Abs 3 EStG (column 8 of the annex ESt 1 2 3 B 1993 and 1994 communication ESt 4 B 1993 and 1994) as well as for the cases of consideration according to the progression proviso (columns 9 and 11 of Annex ESt 1 2 3 B 1993 and 1994 Communication ESt 4 B 1993 and 1994) alternatively determined side by side"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The application of Section 2a (3) EStG is only to be decided when assessing the income tax of the individual participants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The application according to \u00a7 2a Abs 3 EStG can only be made in the income tax declaration of the Stpfl at the tax office of his residence (Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2965 in Annex AUS 1993 and 1994)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Appendix 1 Income from dividends and interest (additional information) 1 General 11 Requirement and verification of documents In the case of dividends and interest, the documents from domestic and foreign banks regarding the amount of the income and the withholding tax withheld (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "