n"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In addition, no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "6 of the guide"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "14 Processing instructions For 1993, the income (income reduced by the proportionate income-related expenses and the proportionate savings allowance and, if applicable,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "if an application according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 34c (2) EStG, after deduction of foreign taxes) in the machine processing in Annex AUS 1993 to the Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2910 -12 -14 -16 -18 -20 -22 -24 and the income is always in the attachment KSO 1993 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "2632/33 to be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The foreign taxes that are no longer subject to a reduction claim in the source country are listed in Annex AUS 1993 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2911 -13 -15 -17 -19 -21 -23 -25 to be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a deduction in accordance with Section 34c (2) EStG, the AUS 1993 annex at Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2984 enter the number of the country for which the foreign tax was deducted when determining the income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "From 1994, the AUS 1994 annex has been separated according to state, - the foreign income from capital assets to the Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2950 -53 -56 -68 -71 -74 -77 -80 -28 and at the same time in the enclosure KSO 1994 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "2632/33 the income-related expenses (without deductible foreign taxes according to Section 34c (2) EStG) to the Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2951 -54 -57 -69 -72 -75 -78 -81 -29 and the foreign taxes to be deducted on request according to \u00a7 34c paragraph 2 EStG to the Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/29 -52 -55 -58 -70 -73 -76 -79 -82 -30"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "2 Tax credit according to the double taxation agreement for France In relation to France, there is the special feature that France grants residents of the Federal Republic of Germany a tax credit (\"avoir fiscal\") on dividends distributed upon application"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the shareholders of French corporations domiciled in the Federal Republic of Germany will not be charged with French capital gains tax or will be refunded in full"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "When assessing German income tax, an amount of 50 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the distribution of the French corporation as a \"tax credit\" such as withheld German capital gains tax offset against or refunded to the German tax of the shareholder"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This amount must also be added to the shareholder's income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The French tax authorities grant the German tax authorities the amount of the tax credit minus the French capital gains tax of 15%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "on the dividend plus credit by way of a fiscal equalization in a special procedure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For this purpose, the tax assessment office enters the total amount included in the tax base as well as the DM amount to be reclaimed from the French tax authorities in the 4 and 5 copies of the RF 1A form to be used for the application for the French credit and forwards the 5 copies provided for the fiscal equalization to the Federal Office immediately for finance too"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The forwarding to the Federal Office of Finance is to be specially noted on the 4 copy intended for the files of the tax office in Section 5 No. 3"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Forms for asserting the tax credit can be obtained from the Federal Office of Finance, Friedhofstrasse 1 53225 Bonn, Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3 Crediting of fictitious taxes According to some DTAs (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Brazil, India, Spain) a crediting of notional foreign withholding taxes on dividends / interest is permitted up to a certain maximum amount; d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Even if no withholding tax or a lower withholding tax is withheld abroad, foreign taxes or foreign taxes are offset in the income tax assessment within the framework of \u00a7 34c EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "on request, a deduction when determining income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "(An overview is given in K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Vogel, DBA Commentary, 2nd edition, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "191 to Art"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "23 printed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": ") A deduction of fictitious taxes when determining the income according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 34c (2) EStG is no longer possible from the 1994 assessment period if the legal transaction (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the acquisition of a security) after 10 11 1993 was completed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "However, the option to deduct remains in the amount of the"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "actually received the tax amount paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the tax actually paid is deducted, the difference between the foreign tax actually paid and the foreign tax that is considered paid is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If only fictitious taxes can be set off because a deduction is not permitted by law, the right to apply for the deduction of other foreign taxes from the same country is not excluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the legal transaction on which the income is based was concluded before 11 11 1993, the deduction of fictitious taxes is only excluded from the assessment period 1996 (Section 34c Paragraph 6 in conjunction with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 52 Paragraph 25 a EStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of the StMBG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Appendix 2 Income from private property (additional information) 11 Taxation rules under the DTAs In most DTAs, the right to tax income from immovable property (renting and leasing of land and buildings, including personal use) is exclusively assigned to the state where the property is located"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the Federal Republic of Germany as the country of residence, this income is exempt and only taken into account for the progression proviso"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "According to some DBAs (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Spain and Switzerland) the right to tax income from immovable property is available to both the country of domicile and the country of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the Federal Republic of Germany as the country of residence, double taxation is eliminated according to the credit method (in detail no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "21 and 33 of the guide)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of negative income, Section 2a EStG (in detail no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "51 of the guideline and Appendix 4), if necessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "also for the negative progression reservation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "12 Tax bases 121 General The income must always be determined in accordance with the provisions of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It should be noted that the degressive depreciation according to Section 7 (5) EStG is excluded for buildings located abroad that were built after December 31, 1982"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "122 Taxation of owner-occupied apartments from the assessment period 1987 For apartments that were owner-used before 1987, the use of value in accordance with Section 21 (2) EStG is only possible within the framework of the transitional regulation of Section 52 (21) sentence 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This means that in the case of apartments for which in VZ 1986 the value in use was taken as the excess of income over income-related expenses, the income is used both for taxation (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "according to the DBA Switzerland) as well as for the progression proviso (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "DBA France) are to be observed, unless the Stpfl gives an irrevocable declaration according to \u00a7 52 Abs 21 S."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3 EStG or has already submitted it in a previous assessment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The owner already uses an apartment for his own residential purposes if the apartment is available to him at any time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "According to this, self-use throughout the whole year within the meaning of Section 21 (2) EStG is generally to be assumed if the apartment is actually only occupied by the Stpfl for a relatively short period of time, but is otherwise available to him at any time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "According to the BFH judgment of 24 September 1985 (BStBl 1986 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "287) by comparing the estimated gross rental value and the proven income-related expenses (R 162 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Owner-occupied apartments that do not come under the transitional regulation of Section 52 (21) sentence 2 EStG are therefore no longer to be taken into account for tax purposes from 1987 onwards"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A credit or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "a deduction of foreign income tax (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "according to the DBA Switzerland) acc"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 34c (1) and (2) EStG is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Apartments abroad that are first used in 1987 or later are not taken into account due to the repeal of Section 21 (2) sentence 1 EStG (Section 52 (21) sentence 1 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The deduction amount according to \u00a7 10e EStG is only granted for apartments located in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Appendix 3 Income from employment or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "dependent work according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "DTA law (additional information) Preliminary remark: The BMF letter of 5 1 1994 BStBl 1994 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "11 re"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the application of the 183-day clause in the taxation of wages according to the double taxation agreements has been taken into account below"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The examples in no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "5 of the BMF letter is also pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "1 Activity for a private employer in a DTA country 11 Principle of the location of the work111 General If a domestic employee works for a private employer in a DTA country, the country of activity regularly has the right to tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the income is to be released subject to progression (for the DBA Italy, no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The DBAs leave i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the Federal Republic of Germany the right to tax if the employee is no longer than 183 days in the tax or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Calendar year in the other country (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "What matters is where the activity is actually carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant where from or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "where the wages are paid or where the employer is based"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Deviations in some DTAs (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "DBA Austria) and mutual agreements remain unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "112 Managing directors and board members of corporations Managing directors and board members of corporations carry out their managerial activities associated with issuing instructions at the company's headquarters (BFH of 15 11 1971 BStBl 1972 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "68)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of simultaneous taxation by the country of residence of the company and the country of residence of the managing director or board member, the initiation of a mutual agreement procedure can be applied for (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "6 of the guide)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The domestically resident managing director of a GmbH who undertakes a business trip abroad, however, carries out his activity abroad because a definable specific business transaction is given (BFH of 21 5 1986 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "739)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The 183-day rule is i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "to be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "113 Temporary employment relationship According to more recent agreements (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "France, Italy, Norway, Sweden) the 183-day rule does not apply to temporary workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In this case, both the state of employment and the state of residence of the employee have a right to tax the wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the foreign tax will be credited or deducted within the framework of \u00a7 34c EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "deducted (also No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "133)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "114 Processing instructions In the assessment procedure, it must be checked whether the requirements for exemption from wages are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the relevant exemption certificates for the purposes of wage tax deduction in accordance with Section 39b (6) EStG have been issued by the permanent establishment tax office (see Section 123 LStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For the progression proviso, the income is to be determined according to German law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Advertising expenses (or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "unused lump sums and tax exemptions), which are related to the foreign activity, are to be taken into account for the income to be recognized in the case of progression proviso"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, they may not reduce domestic income (Section 3c EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The foreign wages are in Appendix N 1993 and 1994 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "47/4839 the advertising expenses are to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "87/8857 to be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Previously incurred income-related expenses that are caused by non-self-employed work abroad reduce the tax rate income (BFH of 6 10 1993 BStBl 1994 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "113)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "115 Prohibition of deduction of special expenses Special expenses (pension expenses) are not deductible if they are directly economically related to tax-free income (Section 10 (2) No. 1 EStG 1990 H 87a (non-deductible pension expenses) EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The reduction in the advance deduction, on the other hand, is not affected, even if there is tax-free wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "12 Amount of the wages to be exempted 121 Current remuneration If the wages in the Federal Republic of Germany are exempt under a DTA, it must first be checked to what extent the remuneration can be allocated to the foreign activity or the domestic activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If an allocation is not possible, the wages are to be divided according to the ratio of the agreed working days abroad to the other agreed working days (BFH of 29 1 1986 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "479 and 513 and examples in no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "61 of the BMF letter of 5 1 1994 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "122 Back payments According to the same principles, a one-off payment (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Anniversary payment), which represents an additional payment for a previous active activity and is proportionally attributable to foreign and domestic activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For the tax exemption, it does not depend on when and where the remuneration is paid, but solely on whether it is paid to the employee for work abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "There is no additional payment for a previous active activity if the one-off payment is used in whole or in part for supply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "13 183-day rule 131 General Taxation remains in the country of residence (= Federal Republic of Germany), provided that the following conditions are all met (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "183-day rule): the employee does not stay in the country of employment for more than 183 days in total during the respective tax year (tax year in the country of employment does not need to be identical to the calendar year), and the remuneration is paid by or for an employer who does not is resident in the country of work, and the remuneration is not borne by a permanent establishment or permanent establishment that the employer has in the country of work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "132 Determination of the 183-day period Requirement for the 183-day rule (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "131) is u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "that the employee does not stay in the country of employment for more than 183 days in total during the respective tax year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The 183-day period is for every tax year or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Check calendar year separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the tax year differs from the calendar year, the tax year of the country of activity is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A different tax year have z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": ": Great Britain 6 4 to 5 4 Ireland 6 4 to 5 4 India1 4 to 31 3 According to some agreements (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "DBA Norway from 1991) is based on a \"period of 12 months\" instead of the calendar or tax year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "When determining the 183 days, the decisive factor is not the duration of the activity, but the physical presence in the country of activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It depends on whether the employee was present in the country of employment for more than 183 days"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This is also the case if you are only present briefly on one day"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Days of attendance in the country of activity include:"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "counted: the day of arrival and departure; In the case of professional drivers, the days of the outward and return journey are not counted. All days of attendance in the country of activity immediately before, during and immediately after the activity, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Saturdays, Sundays, public holidays Days of presence in the country of work during work breaks, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "in the event of strike, lockout, lack of deliveries, illness (unless this prevents the employee from leaving and he would otherwise have met the requirements for exemption in the country of employment), vacation days that are taken immediately before, during and immediately after the work in the country of employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Days of interruption of the activity which are spent exclusively outside the country of activity, as well as times of transit outside of the country of activity are not counted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the employee returns daily to his place of residence in the country of residence, he is present in the country of employment every day"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The BFH judgment of 10 5 1989 BStBl II S, based on other principles"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "755, as before, does not apply beyond the decided individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Several stays in the same contracting state within a tax year for one or more employers must be added together"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "133 Payment by an employer resident in the country of activity Prerequisite for the 183-day rule (no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "131) is u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "that the remuneration is paid by or for an employer who is not resident in the country of activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "According to some DBAs (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Austria, Norway, India) it is a prerequisite that the employer is based in the Federal Republic of Germany (on this point no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "5 Example 6 of the BMF letter of 5 1 1994 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "(and the examples in BB 1982 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "1169))"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Employer i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of the DBA is the entrepreneur who financially bears the remuneration for the work performed (BFH of 21 8 1985 BStBl 1986 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This is the case if the employee owes his work to the foreign company, works under its management and is subject to its instructions and the wages are not part of the price of a delivery or work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the case of international employee leasing, the hirer is to be regarded as the employer in accordance with the purpose of the 183-day rule (comment on Art"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "15 of the OECD MA)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "However, special provisions of the agreements for temporary workers must be observed (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "113)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A permanent establishment cannot be considered as an employer (BFH of 29 1 1986 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "442 and p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "513)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "However, a partnership can be an employer according to the spirit and purpose of the 183-day rule"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the domicile of the employer is determined by the location of the management"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "134 Payment of wages at the expense of a permanent establishment of the employer in the country of employment Prerequisite for the 183-day rule (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "131) is u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "that the remuneration is not borne by a permanent establishment or permanent establishment that the employer has in the country of activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The definition in the respective agreement is decisive for the term \"permanent establishment\""}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "After several DBAs (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "5 DBA Switzerland) is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "a construction or assembly site (in contrast to \u00a7 12 AO) only after a period of 12 months a permanent establishment (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "5 para 2 letter g DBA Switzerland)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The wages are paid at the expense of a foreign permanent establishment if the remuneration is borne economically by the permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It is not decisive who pays the remuneration or who settles the remuneration in his bookkeeping"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The only decisive factor is whether and, if so,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "to what extent the activity carried out abroad according to the respective double taxation agreement (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "7 DBA Switzerland) is to be assigned to the foreign permanent establishment and the remuneration is therefore economically at the expense of the foreign permanent establishment (BFH of 24 2 1988 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "819)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the wages are only part of the settlement of deliveries and services with the permanent establishment, the wages as such are not borne by the permanent establishment (BFH a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "An independent subsidiary (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "GmbH) is not a permanent establishment of the parent company, but may"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "be an employer yourself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "14 DBA Italy The DBA Italy 1925 contained neither the term temporary residence nor the progression proviso"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "As a result, wages were to be exempted for only an hourly job in Italy"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Protocol No. 16 lit."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "e and no 22 lit."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "b to the agreement of 18 10 1989, which came into force on 27 12 1992 together with the double taxation agreement and is to be applied in principle from 1 1 1993, provides for income from employment that is subject to the 183-day rule under the new double taxation agreement, retrospective application from 1990"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Double taxation is avoided for 1990 to 1992 by the fact that a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Italian tax paid is offset against German tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "From 1993 onwards, wages must be taxed or taxed taking into account the 183-day rule"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "to be released with reservation of progression"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "With a decision of 10 11 1993 (BStBl 1994 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "155) and for the so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Pilot cases with the decision of 16 3 1994 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "508) found that there were no serious doubts about the legality of the retroactive application of the new double taxation treaty for income from employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "With the decision of 29 September 1994 the Federal Constitutional Court did not accept the appeal against the BFH decision of 16 3 1994 (pilot cases) for decision"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "(A decision must therefore be made on pending legal remedies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": ") 15 cross-border commuters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "These are employees who work in the border area of \u200b\u200bone state and return daily to their place of residence in the border area of \u200b\u200bthe other state"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "They are generally taxed in the country of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Deviations apply according to the implementation law for cross-border commuters in the Netherlands (BStBl 1986 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "115, last amended by Art"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "2 of the cross-border commuter law of 24 6 1994 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "440)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "(For the application of the AGGrenzgNL decree Nds"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "FinMin of 8 4 1992 RIW 1992 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "510)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "(Also ESt-Kartei Munich, appendix DBA Belgium K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "11 DBA France K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "31/32 DBA Austria K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "61 DBA Switzerland K"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "81) (According to the revision protocol for the double taxation agreement in Switzerland dated December 21, 1992, the taxation of cross-border commuters has been newly regulated since 1994"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "After that, the border zone disappears"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "According to this, a cross-border commuter is any employee who regularly returns to his place of residence in the other country after the end of work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "It is harmless if the employee does not return to their place of residence for up to 60 working days in the calendar year for professional reasons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the country of residence, the country of activity may in future also levy a tax of up to 45% of the gross remuneration, which is offset against German income tax for German commuters like German wage tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": ") Introductory letter of 19 9 1994 BStBl I S on the taxation of German cross-border commuters who work in Switzerland"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "16 Special regulations For artists, athletes, flight and ship personnel, university teachers, students, schoolchildren, apprentices and other trainees, the DTAs contain special, different regulations in some cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "On the taxation of guest teachers BMF letter dated 10 1 1994 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "2 Work for a public employer in a DBA state If the employee works for a public employer, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": ", regardless of the place of activity, the state of the treasury has the right to tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This usually does not apply if the employee has the nationality of the country of employment (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Local staff)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3 Foreign work decree Under the requirements of the foreign work decree (Appendix 32 of the LStR 1993), foreign income from employment is exempted under the progression proviso (entry of wages in Annex N 1993 and 1994 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "47/4836 or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of advertising expenses at Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "87/8857)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In detail, the following requirements must be met: the Stpfl is an employee of a domestic employer, the foreign activity is for a domestic supplier, manufacturer or contractor, the foreign activity is in connection with one of the projects listed in Section I No. 1 to 4 of the foreign activity decree, the foreign activity is exercised in a non-DTA state, there is no wage from a domestic public fund, the duration of the foreign activity is at least three uninterrupted months"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "(See"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "in detail card 11 to \u00a7 34c paragraph 5 ESt-Kartei M\u00fcnchen) Appendix 4 Negative foreign income (additional information) 1 Restriction of loss compensation and deduction according to \u00a7 2a paragraph 1 and 2 EStG11 Negative income \u00a7 2a paragraph 1 and 2 EStG was Assessment period 1983 inserted into the EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For the legal situation 1983 to 1991 Annex 3Ab 1992, \u00a7 2a Paragraph 1 and 2 EStG applies to the following losses / profit reductions: from an agricultural and forestry establishment located abroad (\u00a7 2a Paragraph 1 No. 1 EStG), from a commercial establishment located abroad, who are not actively involved i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of Section 2a Paragraph 2 EStG (Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 2 EStG), from partial value depreciation on shares in foreign corporations that belong to business assets (Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 3 a EStG), from the sale or withdrawal of shares in foreign corporations Corporations that belong to business assets, incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the profit reductions from the dissolution or capital reduction of the foreign corporation (Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 3 b EStG), from the sale of significant investments i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of Section 17 EStG in foreign corporations (Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 4 EStG), from a participation as a silent partner in a commercial enterprise or from participatory loans if the debtor has residence, registered office or management abroad (Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 5 EStG ), from the rental and leasing of immovable property located abroad or material included (Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 6 a EStG), from the rental and leasing of ships, insofar as this income is not actually subject to taxation (Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 6 b EStG), from partial value depreciation or from the transfer (sale or withdrawal) of immovable property / items located abroad or from ships if they belong to a business asset (Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 6 c EStG), from partial value depreciation, as well as from the Selling or withdrawing shares in domestic corporations that belong to business assets, provided that these profit reductions are related to a harmful fact i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 6 EStG (\u00a7 2a Paragraph 1 No. 7 a EStG), from the dissolution or capital reduction of domestic corporations, insofar as the losses are due to a damaging fact in the sense of"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 6 EStG (\u00a7 2a Paragraph 1 No. 7 b EStG), from the sale of significant investments i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 17 EStG to domestic corporations, insofar as the losses are attributable to a harmful offense i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 6 EStG (Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 7 c EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "12 Type of income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Abs 1 EStG 121 General Which type of income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Abs 1 EStG is only determined according to the characteristics given abroad (so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "isolating approach)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The re-qualification of income according to the subsidiarity principle (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Section 20 (3) EStG) due to characteristics present in Germany has no effect on the question of the type of income according to Section 2a (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Example: If a silent participation in a foreign commercial enterprise belongs to the business assets of a domestic business enterprise, the affiliation to the domestic business assets is to be disregarded for the question of the type of income according to \u00a7 2a Abs 1 EStG; Losses from the silent participation therefore fall under Section 2a (1) No. 5 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The general rules apply to the assignment of assets to a foreign permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Belongs z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "a loss-making rental residential property for the business assets of an active commercial foreign permanent establishment (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "due to leasing to employees), the loss must be taken into account in the results of the permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Here it is necessary to check whether the income of the permanent establishment comes almost exclusively from an active activity (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "152)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "122 Income of the same type Income of the same type is basically all of the facts listed under a number, unless they fall under the activity clause of Section 2a (2) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to numbers that are broken down into letters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Numbers 3 and 4 are to be combined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Example: The Stpfl takes a partial write-off on his participation in the Swiss company X-AG, which operates a hotel"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the same assessment period, he made a profit from the sale of his substantial stake in the Swiss company Y"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "-AG that makes weapons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "= There is compensable income according to \u00a7 2a Abs 1 Nr 3 a and b EStG or according to \u00a7 2a Abs 1 Nr 3 a and Nr 4 EStG, depending on whether the participation in Y"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "-AG is held in business or private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "To the income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Abs 1 Nr 7 lit."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "a to c EStG No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "16In the case of jointly assessed spouses, negative income from one spouse according to Section 2a (1) EStG can be offset against positive income from the other spouse of the same type and from the same country (H 5 (joint assessment) EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "13 Income determination The negative income must be determined according to German tax law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "All operating expenses or business expenses that are economically related to the income generated abroad must be taken into account (H 5 (income determination) EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "14 Concept of the state It is the state territory according to international law, even if parts of the state territory should have their own financial or tax sovereignty (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "British Channel Islands, Hong Kong)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "When a state collapses, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the USSR or Yugoslavia, the later offsetting with positive income must be based on the national territory in which the earlier loss would have occurred from today's perspective"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This means that z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Remaining negative income from the former USSR, which accrued in the area of \u200b\u200btoday's Ukraine, can be offset against corresponding positive income from Ukraine, but not against that from Russia"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "15 Income from commercial establishments 151 The general term \u201cpermanent establishment\u201d is only defined in accordance with Section 12 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For each foreign permanent establishment it must be checked separately whether it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "an active activity i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of Section 2a (2) EStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "152)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "152 Activity clause Unrestricted loss compensation is possible in the event of losses from a foreign permanent establishment if the Stpfl proves that the permanent establishment carries out an active activity in accordance with Section 2a (2) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Losses / profit reductions from a participation i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Abs 1 Nr 3 and 4 EStG fully compensatory or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "deductible if the taxpayer proves that the foreign corporation has been active either since it was founded or for the last 5 years before and during the assessment period (Section 2a Paragraph 2 S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "2 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A foreign commercial establishment / foreign corporation is actively active if it has exclusively or almost exclusively the following activities as its object: the production and delivery of goods, except for weapons; the extraction of mineral resources; the establishment of commercial services, except for the construction and operation of Facilities that serve tourism, except for the rental and leasing of economic goods, including"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the transfer of rights, plans, models, procedures, experience and knowledge; holding shares of at least 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "in a foreign corporation, which in turn exclusively or almost exclusively has the aforementioned activities as its object, as well as related financing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Whether a commercial establishment exclusively or almost exclusively an active activity i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of Section 2a Paragraph 2 EStG has to be examined separately for each financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The decisive factor for this is the ratio of gross income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Under gross income, the target income is included without transitory items and without a possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "to understand separately shown VAT"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "They are to be derived from the profit and loss account of the permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the profit is determined in accordance with Section 4 (3) EStG (excess of operating income over operating expenses), the actual income must be used (Section 76 (8) KStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The gross income comes exclusively or almost exclusively from active activity if the passive gross income is 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of the total gross income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For details, see the explanations in Section 76, Paragraph 9, p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "1 - 4 KStR (R 5 Abs 3 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Active income according to Section 2a (2) EStG also includes a loss of sale or abandonment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For the question of whether an active or passive permanent establishment has been sold or given up, the conditions in the financial year of the sale or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "to stop the task taking into account the previous financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "153 Offsetting of permanent establishment results Negative income from a non-active commercial permanent establishment may not be offset against positive income from an active commercial permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Loss offsetting is not possible even with the same business premises if the ratio of inactive to active activity has changed within two assessment periods"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply if the permanent establishment can now be qualified as an active permanent establishment without changing its activity due to a legal change (here: holding function as active activity according to the St\u00c4ndG 1992)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the Stpfl must be presented as if the activity clause had not been changed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "16 Income from participations in corporations with a foreign connection Negative income according to Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 7 EStG, which is indirectly attributable to an offense of No. 1 to 6 realized in the domestic corporation, may be offset by shareholders with positive income from No. 7 if the Income is attributable to facts of the same number or, in the case of numbers 3 and 4, of these two numbers (R 5 para 1 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "A compensation of income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Abs 1 Nr 7 EStG is also permissible with income within the meaning of the respective number, on the facts of which the income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "number 7 (see examples H 5 EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If the domestic corporation in which the participation is held generates mixed income (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "from a domestic commercial enterprise and a foreign agricultural and forestry enterprise), it must be determined whether and to what extent negative income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of Section 2a Paragraph 1 No. 1 to 6 EStG are included in the overall result (here: losses from foreign agriculture and forestry)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "17 Separate determination of the remaining losses For the first time on December 31, 1992, the negative income remaining at the end of an assessment period is to be determined separately with analogous application of Section 10d (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The ESt 2E / 3E form must be used for this (see Appendix 6)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to the purpose of the negative progression proviso"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the separate determination for 1992, the negative income from the assessment periods 1985 to 1991 must also be included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The 7-year limit for the ability to carry losses must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "18 Constitutionality The BFH has ruled the constitutionality of Section 2a (1) EStG - also with regard to the negative progression proviso - in several judgments (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "BFH of 17 10 1990 BStBl 1991 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "136 and from 26 3 1991 BStBl 1991 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "704) confirmed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The decisions of the BFH are based on individual facts of \u00a7 2a Abs 1 EStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "issued before the St\u00c4ndG 1992"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "However, it can be assumed that the BFH considers the provision as a whole to be constitutional even after the amendment by the St\u00c4ndG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Due to pending constitutional complaints, legal remedies according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "To let \u00a7 363 Abs 2 AO rest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Suspension of execution is not to be granted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "2 Loss deduction in accordance with Section 2a Paragraphs 3 and 4 of the Income Tax Act21 Concept of state On the concept of state, no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In contrast to Section 2a Paragraph 1 EStG, Section 2a Paragraph 3 EStG also has to take into account the territorial scope of the respective DTA, which does not have to encompass the entire national territory (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "the DTA with Great Britain does not apply to the British Channel Islands, Hong Kong and the British Virgin Islands and the DTA with Denmark does not apply to the Faroe Islands and Greenland)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "22 Income determination To determine income, no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "13If the Stpfl has several commercial permanent establishments in the foreign country concerned, a loss can only be deducted if, after offsetting against permanent establishment profits from the same country, a loss still remains"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For the calculation of the loss deduction and the later additional amount according to \u00a7 2a Abs 3 S."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "1 and 3 EStG is with positive income from active and possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "inactive commercial establishments in the same foreign country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "23 Activity clause The loss deduction in accordance with Section 2a Paragraph 3 EStG presupposes an active activity of the foreign commercial establishment i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of Section 2a Paragraph 2 EStG (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "152 and H 5 (General) EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "24 Application The application must be submitted to the local tax office (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "by entering the loss in Annex AUS 1993 and 1994 to Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2965)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Also note"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "83 of the guide"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The right to apply must be exercised uniformly for the entire income exempted under the double taxation agreement of all commercial establishments located in a foreign country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The amount of the application cannot be limited"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Participation in a foreign co-entrepreneurship is also considered a permanent establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If a foreign partnership is taxed as a legal person abroad, the application of Section 2a (3) EStG does not prevent this (BFH dated 16 11 1989 BStBl 1990 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "204)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "25 Separate statement Are losses in"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Abs 3 EStG, they must be determined separately and uniformly according to \u00a7 180 Abs 5 AO if several taxpayers are involved in the income, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "if several persons with unlimited tax liability are involved in a foreign co-entrepreneurship or if a domestic co-entrepreneurship in which not only foreign shareholders are involved generates foreign income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "As part of the determination, the factual and legal requirements for the loss deduction must be determined, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "whether there is commercial income and whether the requirements for active activity i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 2a Abs 2 EStG are fulfilled"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, the application for loss deduction according to \u00a7 2a Abs 3 EStG (and a possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "subsequent subsequent taxation) only to be decided when the co-entrepreneur's income tax assessment (H 5 (permanent establishment losses with DBA) EStH 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For the details, no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "83 of the guide"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "26 Progression proviso It should be noted that the negative progression proviso is only to be taken into account in each country if no application has been made pursuant to Section 2a (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the event of subsequent taxation in the following assessment periods, only the amount that is not used for subsequent taxation is subject to the progression proviso"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "27 Subsequent taxation An amount up to the amount of the loss deducted in accordance with Section 2a Paragraph 3 Clause 1 and 2 EStG is to be added back in the following assessment periods for an unlimited period of time, provided that the total of the permanent establishments in the country concerned results in a positive amount (Section 2a Paragraph 3 Clause 3 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Profits from inactive permanent establishments lead to the addition in the case of DBAs without an activity clause (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The additional amount is shown in Annex AUS 1993 and 1994 at Kz"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "19/2966 to be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In the event of a sale, neither the tax exemption according to \u00a7 16 Paragraph 4 EStG nor the reduced tax rate according to \u00a7 34 EStG is to be granted (BFH of 16 11 1989 BStBl 1990 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "204 m"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "There is no subsequent taxation if the taxpayer proves that it is generally not possible to carry forward or carry back losses in the foreign country (Section 2a (3) sentence 4 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "28 Monitoring To monitor subsequent taxation, a monitoring overview (Annex 7) is to be kept, separated by country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Since the obligation to add relates to all permanent establishments in the country in question, overviews must also be set up for losses from permanent establishments that were already sold or abandoned in previous years if the deducted losses have not been fully taxed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Monitoring is also necessary with regard to any future permanent establishments if income is not currently being generated in the country in which the losses were incurred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "3 Universal Succession In the event of inheritance, the negative income not balanced or not offset according to Section 2a Paragraph 1 EStG and the amount deducted and not yet added according to Section 2a Paragraph 3 EStG shall pass to the heir (R 5 Paragraph 5 EStR 1993)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "--- Annex 2: Overview of withholding tax ratesOverview of withholding tax ratesDividenend interestCountry Withholding tax rateReduction in the country of withdrawalTaxes remaining abroad withholding tax rateReduction in the country of withholdingTaxes remaining abroad30 15 15 10 - 10Australia from 010787 - - - Belgium251015251010Denmark301515-- France2025 / 3510 -15 -25 / 025/0-Ireland25-18 29/029/0-Israel25-25 Italy new DBA 324-32430 -30 (15) (10) Japan2051520 10 10 Canada25101525 10 15 Luxembourg convertible and profit bonds15 -15 --- 15 15 -Netherlands Income bonds251015 --- 251015Norway251015 --- Austria from 199220-20 --- 25101522-22Portugal from 198925101525/2010/515 (+ 5) Sweden301515 --- Switzerland border power plants, income bonds, participation of silent partners or par"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Loans3520153535-3530535530Spain from 198920515201010251015251510South Africa15-1510-10USA30151530 / 030/0-General These are the \"normal\" tax rates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In special cases there may be deviations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "If 2 values \u200b\u200bare given for interest, the first value is the withholding tax rate for interest from fixed-income securities, the second value is the rate for interest from deposits at banks"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Note: The other systems were not included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "--- As before, dividends from untaxed profits are subject to withholding tax of 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": ", who on request to 15 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "can be reduced"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "German shareholders in French companies are treated the same as French shareholders for tax purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, in addition to the refund of the full French withholding tax, you will receive a tax credit i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "of 50% of the gross dividend"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "The tax credit is like an advance payment on the German income or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Corporate tax deducted or refunded in the event of overpayment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "However, the tax credit also leads to an increase in the income from the French"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Shares, so that 150% of the gross dividend is to be recorded as a dividend"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Fictitious tax credit according to DTA"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Several special rates and exemptions for certain interest income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "In numerous special cases, the interest is not subject to withholding tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Withholding tax does not apply to - interest payments by Canadian non-resident-owned investment corporations; Interest payments on bonds and other liabilities issued by the Government of Canada, a provincial government, a major broker, a community, certain educational institutions, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "or when interest is paid on a loan liability that is backed by a government guarantee in Canada"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Recently, however, the tax exemption only applies to interest creditors in certain countries announced by administrative guidelines; - Foreign currency interest payments from a Canadian bank from an account held by the non-Canadian recipient in foreign currency; if the interest is paid in relation to the Canadian currency, it is deemed to have been paid in it; - Interest payments to non-dependents on life insurance liabilities outside Canada; - Interest payments by a Canadian corporation to independent persons on long-term loans; such are accepted if no more than a quarter of the loan amount is repayable within five years; - Interest payments on loans secured in rem by real estate located outside of Canada, unless the interest is deductible in determining Canadian income from employment or other property (other than real estate); - Interest payments in Canadian currency to an independent payer on Canadian dollar deposits with foreign branches of Canadian banks or financial institutions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "Dividends and interest payments from Luxembourg holding companies are exempt from withholding tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "For German shareholders, an additional 5% inheritance tax is levied, which is creditable according to \u00a7 34c EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0124427.xml"}, "text": "--- Double taxation agreementBayernBrandenburgAdministrative instructions19941202"}]